  <num>32-173.04</num>
  <heading>Participant conditions of eligibility.</heading>
  <text>To be eligible to participate in the Program, an individual shall:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Be a resident of the District;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>Be unemployed at the time of application to the Program;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(c)</num>
    <text>Be able to engage in regular, full-time employment, as assessed by the grantee; and</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(d)</num>
    <text>Have one or more of the following barriers to employment:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Lack of consistent work history;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>History of a criminal record;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>History of substance abuse;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(4)</num>
      <text>History of mental illness; or</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(5)</num>
      <text>Housing insecurity.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
